This paper is about developing neural architectures for question answering (QA) tasks. The paper discusses the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and bag-of-words modeling, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) research. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
